<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1102" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1102">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/1375.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It is respectfully suggested that authority be granted to advise
                            Americans who insist on returning to Mexico against Consul’s advice that
                            should they be obliged soon to leave Mexico again and find themselves
                            destitute at the border that they should not expect Government aid in
                            reaching their homes in the States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>